      "value": "function normalizeSpecialChars(str) {\n  return str\n    // Quotes & primes → straight\n    .replace(/[\\u2018\\u2019\\u201A\\u201B\\u2032\\u2035]/g, \"'\")   // ' ' ‚ ‛ ′ ‵ → '\n    .replace(/[\\u201C\\u201D\\u201E\\u201F\\u2033\\u2036]/g, '\"')   // \" \" „ ‟ ″ ‶ → \"\n    // Dashes → hyphen-minus\n    .replace(/[\\u2013\\u2014\\u2015\\u2212]/g, '-')               // – — ― − → -\n    // Ellipsis\n    .replace(/\\u2026/g, '...')                                  // … → ...\n    // Spaces\n    .replace(/[\\u00A0\\u2000-\\u200B\\u202F\\u205F\\u3000]/g, ' ')  // non-breaking & fancy spaces → space\n    // Bullets & misc\n    .replace(/[\\u2022\\u2023\\u2043]/g, '*')                     // • ‣ ⁃ → *\n    .trim();\n}\n\n// Example\nconst input = \"{{prod_desc}}\";\n\n\nreturn normalizeSpecialChars(input)",
      "variableName": "prod_desc"
